INSERT INTO mc_product_langs VALUES('2799','1109','1','SAMSUNG GALAXY NOTE 3 N9005 32GB, black','Elegant and original; this premium smartphone lets you collect and share ideas from your daily life in a smart and simple way. Whether you\'re looking for a device to help you think creatively or a powerful set of tools that can help organize your day, the Samsung Galaxy Note 3 N9005 LTE 32GB is the ultimate personal assistant.\n\nThe Samsung Note 3 comes with an updated S-Pen, more advanced than ever before, allowing a high degree of precision for onscreen selection and manipulation. Take outstanding pictures and videos with the 13MP camera.\n\nThe multi-touch Super AMOLED display measures a glorious 5.7 inches, providing the space needed to visualize information in ways not possible on most other phones.\n\nBesides all of that, the Note 3 packs a powerful 2.3 GHz Quad Core processor and the Adreno 330 graphics card, allowing advanced visuals to render flawlessly across the impressive display. And with 32GB of storage, you\'ll have plenty of space to store all your videos, photos, and more.','','1');
INSERT INTO mc_product_langs VALUES('2800','1110','1','APPLE IPHONE 5S 32GB, gold','Newer, faster, better A 64-bit architecture chip, fingerprint identity technology, the finest optic engineering, and fully loaded OS come together to make the iPhone 5S. The phone is eons ahead of its time, and is quite the technological marvel. The colors of the iPhone 5S have been chosen based on how they stand in a worldly view- how much of the color is seen around us, how appealing is it to the human eye. Rest assured that all of these colors are known to have value and elicit a particular emotion. We made certain associations with the colors, and this has been scientifically proven. All the colors of the iPhone 5S will draw out certain sentiments in you.\nTouch ID. Your phone. Your identity. A user checks and uses his phone countless number of times. Entering a passcode each time can be quite a pain. There is also the matter of security. While a passcode can be stolen, a fingerprint cannot. With iPhone 5S, accessing your phone is easier, quicker, and much more personal; not to mention futuristic. With Touch ID, a new fingerprint identity sensor, you have to simply place your finger on the home screen to unlock the phone.\n','{&quot;Brand&quot;:&quot;Apple&quot;,&quot;Color&quot;:&quot;Gold&quot;,&quot;Operating System&quot;:&quot;IOS 7&quot;,&quot;Resolution&quot;:&quot;640 x 1136 pixels&quot;,&quot;Storage Capacity&quot;:&quot;32 GB&quot;,&quot;Width&quot;:&quot;58.6 mm&quot;,&quot;CPU Speed&quot;:&quot;1.7 Ghz&quot;,&quot;Wireless Connections&quot;:&quot;Yes, 802.11a\\/b\\/g\\/n Wi-Fi&quot;,&quot;Standby time&quot;:&quot;Up to 250 hours&quot;,&quot;Phone camera&quot;:&quot;8 Megapixel&quot;,&quot;Operating frequency&quot;:&quot;850, 900 ,1800,1900&quot;,&quot;User Interface&quot;:&quot;Touchscreen&quot;,&quot;Product weight&quot;:&quot;132 grams&quot;,&quot;CPU&quot;:&quot;Dual core 1.7 GHz&quot;}','1');
